There are two ways to do this. One, in the repeat command itself, you can
specify a time between each repeat in seconds.

From the help file:
/repeat

  Usage:

  /REPEAT [-w[<world>] [-<time>] <count> <command>

If you set the time to "-0" the commands will go out as fast as tf can
send them.

Another solution, which I use since I never liked the 1 second default
delay, is to add "/set ptime=0" in your .tfrc. This sets the default
repeat time to 0.

Beware, however, in that this can cause mistaken repeat commands to
become very spammy very fast.

-Clay


