Heres my page hilight, working, and only hilighting recipient if it's 
more then just 'you' and adding a recipient list to the line if none was 
present in the page format.
Also included is a macro /setpage which will set the page #prepend format 
appropriately in the current world, assuming you are using MUFpage by 
Foxen.  Any other page that allows prepends you're on your own..  As I 
said, the format needs to be:
##PAGE> From_name #<># To_list #><# Message <EGAP## Origonal page format
Where the from_name doesn't have a space in it (If names can have spaces, 
change the ([^ ]+) to (.+)), the To_list is a comma seperated list of 
names without spaces (As in PersonA or PersonA, PersonC and PerconC).  
This will probably puke if the message has a #><# or <EGAP## surrounded 
by spaces in it, but how likely is that?
NOTE: Change attributes to taste.  In addition you might want to add a /beep.

/def -q -p1000 -F -mregexp \
-t'^##PAGE> ([^ ]+) #<># ([^ ]+((, [^ ]+)* and [^ ]+)?) #><# (.*) <EGAP##' \
catchpage = \
  /if (strlen(%P3)) \
    /def -p999 -F -mregexp -t\"($(/escape \(\)\[\]\|\*\+\?\.\\ %P2))\" -P1Ccyan pageto %; \
  /else \
    /def pageto %; \
  /endif %; \
  /def -p998 -F -mregexp -t\"($(/escape \(\)\[\]\|\*\+\?\.\\ %P5))\" -P1BCblue pagebody %; \
  /def -q -p997 -F -mregexp -t\"($(/escape \(\)\[\]\|\*\+\?\.\\ %P1))\" -P1Cyellow pagefrom = \
    /undef pageto %%; \
    /undef pagebody %%; \
    /undef pagefrom %; \
  /if (strstr(%PR,%P2) >= 0) \
    /substitute %PR %; \
  /else \
    /substitute %PR (To %P2) %; \
  /endif
/def setpage = p #prepend ##PAGE> %%n #<># %%t #><# %%m <EGAP##

