> Any suggestions appreciated.
> Mung.
> I use version 3.5 a20 btw


	Triggers have priorities, and the higher priority ones get tried
first.  So you can make a trigger which does nothing at a higher
priority than the one which gags:


/def -p2 -t'VIDINFO - Richard enters the room.' vid_dont_gag =
/def -p1 -ag -t'VIDINFO - * enters the room.' vid_gag =


