This is going to have one very big problem; very few function keys
actually send out two '[' characters in a row.  However, a great many of
them send an escape character followed by a '['; it just so happens that
ESC looks something like '^[' or a weird '[' on most systems.

In any case, two '[' characters probably isn't going to match anything.
The fix here is to put the literal escape in; this varies according to
your editor, but in vi you go

/bind ^V^[\[17~ = <action>

(where ^V is Control-V and ^[ is ESC).
