The change (in 3.5 alpha 9) was only in the *display* of nonprintable
characters that made it to the output because they were not first
matched by a keybinding: before, they were ignored; now, they are printed
in bold reverse printable form.  It has absolutely no effect on keybindings.

If you have a key that emits "^[[17", then the correct way to bind it
in all versions since 2.1 is
  /def -b'^[[17~' name = body    (quotes are optional in this case)
or
  /bind ^[[17~ = body
