Actually, that does matter immensely.

The reason is that the speed of the `connection' between your virtual 
console and your computer is PDF (pretty damn fast).  TF is actually 
sending multiple bells to your terminal, but they transfer so fast that 
you hear them all at the same time (effectively).

You can notice this if you pop up an xterm, create a file containing 10 
^G characters, and then cat it to the screen.  By all rights, you should 
get 10 bells, but because the connection is as fast as it is you only get 
the one.

If you were on a 110-baud Teletype going in off a phone line, you would 
definitely hear multiple bells.
