Yes; you can set the environment variable TFLIBDIR to the correct directory.
For example, under the Bourne shell or derivatives you would type
$ TFLIBDIR=~/tf-lib
$ export TFLIBDIR
or under the C shell you (might; I'm not quite sure) type
% setenv TFLIBDIR ~/tf-lib

