I had this problem too, it's not the command as such, but the name of the
alias. Alias are done by creating a send-hook. So you send the "1", and
a send-hook catches it before it is sent to the mud and replaces it by
the true commands.

I think you are using speedwalk or map or something like this. They have
a send hook for numbers, catching them, trying to perform their tasks,
and if they see it's not part of their special task to catch this special
number, they send it to the mud via /send.

So what you do is
- send "1" to the mud (with this send hook from speedwalk or map or whatever),
  that's the "Huh?!?"
- send the commands asigned to the alias, that's the spells.

I decided that for me the numbers for alias are important, so I do not use
map and speedwalk any more ...


