I have verified this myself, please don't send any more reports.  It
seems to occur when tf reads multiple keystrokes at once; this could
happen for example when running tf remotely over a slow connection
(modem), or when tf is very busy doing other things.  I'll fix it
of course, but as always I can't say when.

There are better alternatives to holding arrow keys anyway.  To move
large distances, it's usually better to use the word movement commands
(^B and ^F by default, ^[b and ^[f if you /load kb-emacs.tf or
kb-bash.tf), go to the beginning of the line with ^A, etc.  Then you
know where the cursor will be without counting characters or waiting
for the screen to catch up.  See: /help keys.

