damalas wrote:
> 
> HI..never did get an answer on the exact last step to save a mapped path
> to a <pathname.tf> file. I have a ton of them done..the format created
> uses /dopath, but like I said before, I have forgotten how the heck I did it!
> 
> Steps:
> 1. /mark
> 2. /savepath <pathname>
> 3. /save -a <pathname> -i <pathname.tf>
> 
> My problem is in step 3. It used to produce a file named <pathname.tf>
> with a /dopath format. Can anyone remember how to do the last step right,
> or spot where I am making my mistake?
> 
> Talia
> 

You can also define the following lines in your .tfrc:

/def -i MAPFILE   = ~/tf-dir/pathfile.tf
/~def_file_command load map MAP
/~def_file_command save map MAP -i = /dopath *
/def -i listmap = /list -i = /dopath *

With these definitions you only have to write /savemap to save
your paths to a file (note however that it overwrites the file so
have all the paths loaded when you use this command) and /loadmap.

Ingar

