You could also try
   /def -mregexp -p50 -F -t'Ayla' sub_Ayla = /substitute %{PL}(C)Ayla%{PR}
which, rather than forcing the regular expression to match the whole line,
which is slow and inefficient (as I understand it :), uses special tf
substitutions to put in the text before (%{PL}) and after (%{PR}) the
regular expression which was matched. Basically, it's the same thing,
though.

