sending another command right after 'affect'.  Then what you do in your
spellup macro is clear the flags, send 'affect', let your detection
triggers work.  And then you have another trigger on 'End of spells.'
which then sends the commands to activate all of the appropriate
triggers.  If you have no nice way of generating the 'End of spells.'
kind of message, you could instead use /repeat to run the activation
macro after a certain delay (1-2 seconds probably).



