Assuming you want to do that inside a macro (not on the command line),
the /eval is not necessary; just use

  /set counter=$[counter + 1]

You could also use
 
  /test counter := counter + 1

There is no builtin shorthand like C's ++ operator, but you could write
a macro:

  /def inc = /test %1 := %1 + 1

and use it like this:

  /inc counter

