How about trying "/set wrap=off"? This will prevent TF from perturbing
the output from the MUD with linesfeeds. That way your terminal can do the
wrapping itself, and will allways wrap on the right column, and at the same
time, giving you cut'n'paste possibilities for lines longer then one
physical window line. This is true for example with xterm, where you can
normally cut'n'paste with lines longer then then width of the xterm, and
still have it treated as one line at paste time.
I hope that helps.

