In TF, do:

/def -p100 -ag -mglob -t'FugueEdit > *' = /grab %-2
/savedef

And make sure you /loaddef in your .tfrc


On the Tinymush, stick a command on yourself like so:

&C-ED me=$ed */*:@pemit %#=FugueEdit > &%1 %0=[switch(%1,
         name,[fullname(locate(%#,%0,*))],[get([locate(%#,%0,*)]/%1)])]

All in one line. Then you can do:

ed OBJECT/attribute to bring it into your edit window for changes.

ed OBJECT/name to edit the 'fullname' of an object..for an exit with 3 lines
 of aliases. :)

The locate is there so that the command can be on an object you own, if you
 don't want to put it on yourself. If you put it on an object, you might have
 to tinker with the object (or you) being set INHERIT.

